Yes, those aren’t the right calls to change configuration settings. They have changed over the last few years, especially with the move to Phoenix 6.

For example, to set the motor to inverted, it’d be wristConfig2.MotorOutput.Inverted = InvertedValue.CounterClockwise_Positive or wristConfig2.MotorOutput.Inverted = InvertedValue.Clockwise_Positive.

The TalonFXConfiguration API is documented here. You can look through that list and use the Field names on top of your wristConfig2 variable. Each FieldType variables may have additional variables within it too. For example: wristConfig2.Feedback.FeedbackSensorSource.
